This paper deals with the problem of codebook-based hybrid precoder and combiner design for spatial multiplexing transmission in a mmWave MIMO system. This involves the use of signal processing techniques to optimize the transmission of multiple data streams over a wireless channel. The paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category, as it deals with the optimization of communication systems. It may also belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category, as it deals with the design of wireless networks. The paper may also be relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category, as it involves the use of control theory to optimize the transmission of data. Additionally, the paper may be relevant to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category, as it deals with the transmission of multimedia data over a wireless channel. Finally, the paper may be relevant to the Computation and Language (cs.CL) sub-category, as it involves the use of algorithms to optimize the transmission of data.
